\bentry

\num{3} rADiyilalxda; bagagxDavilalxda; kadaDada; kalakilalxda. 
\num{4} toLaguva; beLaguva; ujajxvXlavAda; kAMtiyuta; parxkAshamAnavAda: \eng{clear dawn} parxkAshamAnavAda uSaHkAla. 
\num{5} shudadhx; niSakxLaMka; niduRSaTx; doVSarahita: niSakxlamxSa; kaLaMkarahita: \eng{clear conscience} niSakxLaMka manasusx; shudAdhxMtaHkaraNa; shudAdhxMtaraMga; tapipxtasathxnalalxveMba manoVBAva. 
\num{6} sapxSaTxvAda; suPxTavAda; edudx kANuva; edudx toVruva: \eng{a clear photograph} suPxTavAda CAyAcitarx. 
\num{7} nisasxMdigadhxvAda; saMdigadhxteyilalxda; sulaBagArxhayx; sulaBavAgi--tiLiyuva, garxhisabahudAda, athaRvAguva: \eng{clear answers} nisasxMdigadhxvAda utatxragaLu. 
\num{8} toDakilalxda; goVjilalxda: jaTilavalalxda; eDarutoDarilalxda: toDaku, goVju, toMdare, inonxMdara saMpakaR \mo vugaLilalxda. 
\num{9} parxkaTavAda; vayxkatxvAda; vishadavAda; saMdeVha yA goMdalakekx eDeyilalxde sapxSaTxvAgi kANutitxruva. 
\num{10} sUkaSxmX viveVcaneyuLaLx; sUkaSxmXgArxhi; oLahoguva; tiVkaSxNXdaqSiTxya: \eng{a clear mind} sUkaSxmX viveVcaneyuLaLx manasusx. 
\num{11} Baravaseya. 
\num{12} KaMDita; Kare; nisasxMshaya; Kacita; daqDha; nishicxta. 
\num{13} sulaBashArxvayx; sapxSaTxvAgi, cenAnxgi--keVLisuva; suPxTavAgi keVLibaruva. 
\num{14} (lABa, veVtana \mo vugaLa \vi) nivavxLa; baTu; kaDitavilalxda; kaLeyabeVkAgilalxda. 
\num{15} (saMdeVha, AroVpa, sAla \mo vugaLiMda) tolagisikoMDa; dUravAda; mukatxvAda; nivAraNeyAda; saMbaMdha kaDidukoMDa: \eng{he kept clear of her} avanu avaLiMda dUravidadxnu. 
\num{16} pUtiR; pUrA; iDiV; saMpUNaR: \eng{three clear days} pUtiR mUru dinagaLu. 
\num{17} taDeyilalxda; saliVsAgiruva; bAdhakagaLilalxda; aDacaNeyilalxda; aDiDxyilalxda; sarAgavAda: \eng{a clear road} aDetaDeyilalxda dAri. 
\num{18} (dAsAtxnu, sAmAnu \mo vanunx) iLisida; horategeda. 
\num{19} (Asitx \mo vugaLa meVle) toDakilalxda; sAlada horeyilalxda; nirupAdhika; nibARdhita; sAlasoVla, pUvARdhi \mo vugaLilalxda.

\noindent

\num{2} (aBipArxya, bareha \mo vanunx) sapxSaTxgoLisu; nisasxMdigadhxgoLisu; suPxTagoLisu. 
\num{3} niraparAdhiyeMdu GoVSisu; tapipxtasathxnalalxveMdu toVrisu; nidoRVSiyeMdu--sAdhisu, parxtipAdisu. 
\num{4} (vayxkitxyu rahasayx samAcAravanunx paDeyalu ahaRneMdu) sAru; GoVSisu. 
\num{5} bahiSAkxra yA aDacaNegaLiMda--dUravAgisu, mukatxvAgisu yA biDugaDe koDisu. 
\num{6} aDiDx aDacaNegaLanunx nivArisu; parxtibaMdhaka pariharisu; aDacaNe, anapeVkiSxta vasutx \mo vanunx tegeduhAku, nivArisu: \eng{clear out of the way} dAriyiMda (aDacaNeyanunx) tegeduhAku; dAri biDisu. 
\num{7} (sAla, bilulx \mo vanunx pUtiR) koTuTx biDu; pAvati mADu; tiVrisu; salilxsu. 
\num{8} (cekukx yA vAyxpArada huMDigaLanunx tiVruve maneyalilx) vileVvAri mADu. 
\num{9} baridu mADu; tegedu hAku: \eng{clear a ship of her cargo} sAmAnanunx iLisi haDaganunx KAli mADu. \eng{clear this land of trees} I neladiMda maragaLanunx tegedu hAku yA kaDidu hAku. 
\num{10} (\kanmu\ hAruvudariMda) muTaTxde, tAgade--dATu, hAyu; hAduhoVgu: \eng{the ship cleared the reef} haDagu dibabxvanunx (tAgade) dATitu. \eng{the winner cleared six feet} jayashAliyu kaMbiyanunx tAgade Aru aDi hAridanu. 
\num{11} (haDagu, saraku \mo vugaLa) suMka \mo\ elalxvanUnx tiVrisi--biDisu, biDugaDe mADisu. 
\num{12} (haNavanunx) nivavxLa lABavAgi paDe; kaLeyuvudu, kUDuvudu yAvudU ilalxde oTuTx lABavAgi yA AdAyavAgi paDe. 
\num{13} (vecacxgaLanunx) saridUgisu; tiVrisu; vecacxgaLanenxlAlx koTuTxbiDu. 
\num{14} (yAvudeV sarakina \vi) mArATa mADi mugisu; iruvudanenxlAlx mAri yA koMDu mugisu: \eng{bidders quickly cleared the market's wheat stores} mArukaTeTxya goVdhi dAsAtxnanunx daLALxLigaLu beVga mugisibiTaTxru. 
\num{15} (sAla \mo vugaLiMda) biDisu; biDugaDegoLisu; mukatxgoLisu; vimoVcanegoLisu: \eng{she had to borrow money to clear her estate} avaLu tananx jamiVnanunx biDisikoLaLxlu sAla tegeyabeVkAyitu. \eng{just a few dollars more would clear him} inunx kelaveV kelavu DAlaru avananunx sAladiMda mukatxgoLisutatxve. 
\num{16} (aMce kAgada, TeliphoVnu kare \mo vanunx) vileVvAri mADu; vayxvasethxgoLisu. 
\num{17} anumati koDu; opipxge koDu.

\noindent
\gl{\akirx}
\bmng
\bnum

\num{2} (maMju, cihenxgaLu \mo vu) mAyavAgu; ilalxvAgu; karagihoVgu.

\bnum
\num{1} \eng{accidental colour} bAhayxvalalxda, manasisxge mAtarx goVcaravAguva--baNaNx.

\num{3} \eng{dead colour} (vaNaRcitarxNadalilx) nijiRVva vaNaR; modala--toDeta, baLita; parxthama leVpana; kAMtiyilalxda, hoLapilalxda, nijiRVvavAda--modala toDeta.

\num{6} \eng{man, woman, etc. of colour} vaNiRVya; shevxVtavaNiRVyaralalxda niVgorxV \mo\ janAMgadavaru. 
\num{7} \eng{secondary colours} janayxvaNaRgaLu; yAvudeV eraDu mUlavaNaRgaLanunx berasuvudariMda uMTAguva itara baNaNxgaLu. 
\num{8} \eng{water colours} jalavaNaRgaLu; niVrubaNaNxgaLu; eNeNxyoDanalalxde niVrinoDane berasuva baNaNxgaLu.
